I"#<p>Depression is an experience that is manifests in our mental, emotional and physical experience.</p>

<p>It is characterised by an intense preoccupation with negative thinking about our past, current and future self. </p>

<p>These ways of thinking are accompanied by an emotional experience of meaninglessness and ‘apathy’, which is the loss of interest or pleasure in life.</p>

<p>People experiencing depression also experience changes to their physical state, such as increased tiredness and fatigue and difficulty concentrating. </p>
